    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="159" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <head>No. 34.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                    Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-03-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 29,
                            1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your letter of the 28th instant, requesting that inquiries may be made into
                        the circumstances attending the arrest of Mr. James L. White, a naturalized
                        American citizen, who has been for some months imprisoned in Naas jail under
                        the protection of person and property act (Ireland), and I have to state to
                        you that your application is under the consideration of Her Majesty’s
                        Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GRANVILLE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
